Basic React App
This project is a simple React application built as part of a MERN stack task. The purpose of this app is to familiarize myself with the core concepts of React, including components, JSX, and basic state management.

Project Overview
This application serves as the starting point for creating dynamic user interfaces using React.js. It renders a basic layout with React's core structure and serves as a foundation for further learning in the MERN stack.

Features
React functional components
JSX rendering
React useState for basic state management
Live reloading with npm start
Installation and Setup
To run this project locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:


git clone https://github.com/yourusername/basic-react-app.git


cd basic-react-app


npm install


bash

npm start

The app will be running at http://localhost:3000/.

Technologies Used
React.js - JavaScript library for building user interfaces
HTML/CSS - For basic styling and layout
JavaScript (ES6+) - Logic and functionality
 
